# __PKG_NAME__

A minimal [BigConfig](https://www.bigconfig.ai) package, scaffolded from the
`create-clj-bigconfig-package` skill. It depends on the BigConfig Clojure SDK
(`big-config`) and renders one template through a single `hello` stage.

## Commands

```bash
clojure -M:test                 # run tests (cognitect test-runner)
bb run help                     # run the CLI through the launcher entry point
bb run package validate
bb run package describe
bb run package build
bb run package create     # safe demo create; renders hello
bb run package delete     # explicit no-op
```

## Layout

```
__PKG_NAME__/clojure/
├── run                       # launcher entry point (copied by bc-pkg; safe defaults only)
├── deps.edn                  # one root manifest; src/clj + src/resources on :paths
├── bb.edn                    # runtime deps for `bb run`
├── src/
│   ├── clj/__PKG_NS_SRC_PATH__/   # NOTE: hyphens -> underscores in source paths
│   │   ├── cli.clj           # main* dispatcher
│   │   ├── options.clj       # active profile (`bb`)
│   │   ├── params.clj        # BC_PAR_* overrides -> opts
│   │   ├── tools.clj         # the `hello` render stage
│   │   ├── validation.clj    # pure validate-report + workflow step
│   │   ├── describe.clj      # pure describe-report + workflow step
│   │   └── package.clj       # lifecycle verbs + __PKG_NAME__* wrapper
│   └── resources/__PKG_NS_RES_PATH__/tools/hello/greeting.txt   # hyphens kept
└── test/clj/__PKG_NS_SRC_PATH__/
```

## Grow it

- Add params to the profile in `options.clj` (and `default-profile` in `run`), keeping
  keys kebab-case keywords to match template variables.
- Add a stage: write a render fn in `tools.clj`, register it in `package.clj`'s
  `tool-workflows`, and add it to the `build` and `create` pipelines (and any real
  `delete` pipeline).
- Override any param at runtime with `BC_PAR_*` env vars (e.g. `BC_PAR_NAME=alice`).
- Generated output lands in `.dist/` — never edit it as source.
